<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="37" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="37">A riverine tiger beetles species recorded on sandy bank (per. obs.).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="37" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="37">
Although 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. discreta subsp. elaphroides" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" rank="subSpecies" species="discreta" subSpecies="elaphroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">C. discreta elaphroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is active mainly during sunlight hours on the river banks, it was also noted as species actively hunting during heavy rain on vertical surfaces (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1649/0010-065X-73.2.408" author="Cabrera, G" journalOrPublisher="The Coleopterologists Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" pagination="408 - 410" refId="B9" refString="Cabrera, G, Nuneza, OM, Wiesner, J, Jaskula, R, 2019. Hunting in the rain: unusual behaviour in tiger beetle Cylindera discreta elaphroides in tropical forest in Cebu Island, Philippines (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae). The Coleopterologists Bulletin 73 (2): 408 - 410, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1649/0010-065X-73.2.408" title="Hunting in the rain: unusual behaviour in tiger beetle Cylindera discreta elaphroides in tropical forest in Cebu Island, Philippines (Coleoptera: Cicindelidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1649/0010-065X-73.2.408" volume="73" year="2019">Cabrera et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Some specimens were also observed resting on the leaves of 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Poaceae" genus="Pennisetum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pennisetum" order="Graminales" pageId="0" pageNumber="37" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="37">Pennisetum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. along the river (pers. obs.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
